This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Shaquille Kendall Cole appeared by video.  Attorney Nicholas M Weege in court for Shaquille Kendall Cole.  Prosecuting attorney M Samir Siddique in court for the State of Wisconsin. Status conference held. Defense needs to scheduled TAD evaluation. Updated contact information provided to the Court. Case is adjourned in Branch 30.
Status conference scheduled for November 30, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Shaquille Kendall Cole appeared by video.  Attorney Nicholas M Weege appeared by video for Shaquille Kendall Cole.  Prosecuting attorney Foley J. Van Lieshout in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for a status conference. Defense is in receipt of discovery but no offer and requests time to review material with client. Defenses informs the court that the defendant will complete a TAD evaluation. Case adjourned.
Status conference scheduled for October 27, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Shaquille Kendall Cole in court.  Sarah Dahdouh appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case in court for status conference.   Indigency hearing proceeded.  Based upon the defendant's statements, the court found the defendant eligible for appointment of counsel at county expense.  The court appointed Attorney Nicholas Weege to represent the defendant; counsel to be paid at the rate of $100.00 per hour. The court ordered the defendant to repay Milwaukee County for attorney fees at the rate of $50.00 per month beginning on 11/1/2022 and then the 1st of each month there after.  Failure to make timely payments according to the imposed payment schedule may result in a civil judgment, subject to tax intercept. Order Appointing Attorney at County Expense signed and filed. Case remains calendared in Branch 30.  Status conference scheduled for September 9, 2022 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Shaquille Kendall Cole in court.  Sarah Mackenzie Dahdouh appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for a status of counsel. Defendant does not qualify for public defender representation, but would like to retain counsel.
Case adjourned.  Status conference scheduled for August 19, 2022 at 11:00 am.

Defendant Shaquille Kendall Cole in court.  Navjot Singh Hira appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for pretrial conference/status of counsel.  
Defendant does not qualify for public defender representation.  Indigency Hearing held. 
Court found defendant is NOT eligible for appointment of counsel by the court.  
Case adjourned back to Br 30 for status of counsel. Case remains calendared in Branch 30.  Status conference scheduled for July 18, 2022 at 08:30 am.
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Shaquille Kendall Cole in court.  Emily S Zimmel appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Richards, Branch 30. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel. Defendant does not qualify for Public Defender representation. Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Branch 30.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for June 2, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 04/28/2022@02:00pm
